    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_24_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_24",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a meticulously maintained 2004 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Carbon Black. At the heart of this machine is the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and high-pressure double VANOS variable valve timing, delivering a linear power band up to an 8,000 RPM redline. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a crisp Getrag 420G six-speed manual transmission and a variable M differential lock for optimal corner-exit traction. This example features documented subframe reinforcement and a recent VANOS overhaul, ensuring structural and mechanical integrity. The suspension retains its factory-tuned MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear geometry, providing the communicative feedback and lateral grip these chassis are renowned for. Minor cosmetic patina consistent with age is present, but the drivetrain remains robust, making this an ideal specimen for the purist driver.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 46
    },
    {
